727770f-c.text:
Queens Boulevard at the S.E. corner of Sixty-eighth Avenue (formerly Occident Street, showing in three views the George Herring residence, forwerly known as 47O Queens Boulevard. The house seen in the views was owned and built bv the above named individual in 1898. Views one and two show the house prior to the advance of modern New York City to this area. View No. three shows it afterwards. Some of the outbuildinggs seen in the views
lie in Sixty-eighth Averue (Occident Street).
April 1923
View 2: February 1924
View 3: October 1928.
Nmigene L. Armbruster Collection
